A helicopter pilot is dead after he walked into the aircraft's spinning rotor while giving rides at a Pennsylvania fair.

Carl Enlow, 69, was killed when he was hit by the rotor on Friday night at the Bloomsburg Fair.

The fair's superintendent of police and parking Bill Barratt said the helicopter was refueling when Enlow went back to speak to the pilot who relieved him. Barrett said Enlow's hat blew off his head and he was struck by the rotor when he reached for it.

'He went back to talk to the other pilot, and that's when the rotor struck him,' he said.

