Enlow of Reading was transported by Life Flight to Geisinger Medical Center in Danville, where he died.

Barratt said Enlow was an experienced pilot, having flown helicopters for 50 years including in the military.

'That just goes to prove that anything can happen,' Barratt told PA Homepage.

Dawn Kingston of Bloomsburg told the news website that Enlow was a well-known fixture at the fair, having taken rides for many years.

