'I'm sure that a lot of people who return to the fair probably know him,' she said.

She said Enlow enjoyed helping other people and last year he fulfilled the dying wish of a six-year-old Hazleton girl battling cancer by taking her on a flight.

'He was a very sweet man with a heart of gold, and we really appreciated everything he did,' she said.

Heritage Rotors has been giving helicopter rides since 1993 and is a popular attraction at the fair.

